{"word":"G2135 - εὐνοῦχος - eunoûchos - yoo-noo'-khos - Eunuch","sections":[{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">εὐνοῦχος</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong><span class=\"transliteration\">eunoûchos</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong><span class=\"phonetic\">yoo-noo'-khos</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong><span class=\"short-definition\">Eunuch</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>இலக்கண சொல்வகை / Part(s) of speech: </strong>Noun Masculine / பெயர்ச்சொல் (ஆண்பால்)</span>"},{"paragraph":"அண்ணகர் - ஆண்பால் பெயர்ச்சொல்"},{"paragraph":"1. an emasculated man, a eunuch"},{"paragraph":"2. one who voluntarily abstains from marriage"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English: </strong>From <b>&#x03B5;&#x03C5;&#x0313;&#x03BD;&#x03B7;&#x0301;</b> <b>eune&#x0304;</b> (a <i>bed</i>) and <a href=\"#/G2192 - ἔχω - échō - ekh'-o/2192\">G2192</a>; a <i>castrated</i> person (such being employed in Oriental bed chambers); by extension an <i>impotent</i> or <i>unmarried</i> man; by implication a <i>chamberlain</i> (<i>state officer</i>): - eunuch.</span>"},{"paragraph":""}]}